`KubeColor` is an interface that abstracts away many cases of handling colors, like colors from `DyeColor`, `ChatFormatting` or `TextColor`.

KubeJS injects an implementation of `KubeColor` into the aforementioned classes, so the following instance methods will be present on them as well.

# Instance methods

The following examples will refer to the instance of a class implementing `KubeColor` as `[js]color`.

### `getArgb`

```js
color.getArgb()
color.argb // read-only bean
```

**Return value**
An integer representing the color in `AARRGGBB` format.

---

### `getRgb`

```js
color.getRgb()
color.rgb // read-only bean
```

**Return value**
An integer representing the color in `RRGGBB` format.

In case the implementing class is:
- `DyeColor`: it returns its text color in `RRGGBB`.
- `TextColor`: it returns its value.

---

### `getFireworkRGB`

```js
color.getFireworkRGB()
color.fireworkRGB // read-only bean
```

**Return value**
An integer representing the color in `RRGGBB` format.
In case the implementing class is `DyeColor`, it returns its firework color in `RRGGBB` instead, which is different from text color returned by `[js]getRgb()`.

